WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:02.935
[ Explosion ]

00:02.937 --> 00:04.937
Provenza:
<i>Previously on "Major Crimes"...</i>

00:04.939 --> 00:07.339
Sharon: An hour ago,
a bomb went off in East L.A.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.974
I am a friend of
Albert Luna's.

00:08.976 --> 00:11.110
This could be connected
to his ex-wife.

00:11.112 --> 00:12.444
Buzz: Liseth Ortiz.

00:12.446 --> 00:13.846
He blamed her for everything
that happened.

00:13.848 --> 00:15.681
Cristian murdered
Liseth's father

00:15.683 --> 00:17.950
so that she would come
to his funeral.

00:17.952 --> 00:19.118
When is the service?

00:19.120 --> 00:21.120
[ Explosion ]

00:21.122 --> 00:23.689
<i> Shit. Holy shit.</i>

00:23.691 --> 00:25.657
[ High-pitched ringing ]

00:25.659 --> 00:27.292
♪♪

00:27.294 --> 00:29.128
<i> Pilot: Uh, Control, Air 10,</i>

00:29.130 --> 00:31.497
<i> we've got a confirmed</i>
<i> explosion, Rosedale Cemetery.</i>

00:31.499 --> 00:33.365
<i> Confirmed explosion.</i>

00:33.367 --> 00:34.967
<i> I'm gonna need additional</i>
<i> units. Uh, you --</i>

00:34.969 --> 00:37.369
<i> Just send everybody</i>
<i> at this point.</i>

00:37.371 --> 00:39.138
<i> This -- this looks bad.</i>
<i> Woman over radio:</i>
<i>Units responding to the bombing</i>

00:39.140 --> 00:41.473
<i>are needed on the east side</i>
<i>of Normandie Avenue.</i>

00:41.475 --> 00:43.342
[ Siren wailing ]
<i> Man over radio:</i>
<i> South 17 responding.</i>

00:43.344 --> 00:45.377
<i> Man: South 21 en route.</i>
<i> Man: LAFD responding, code 3.</i>

00:45.379 --> 00:46.979
I'm looking for casualties.

00:46.981 --> 00:48.847
<i> Woman: Air 10, as per LAFD,</i>

00:48.849 --> 00:52.051
<i> please advise on a preliminary</i>
<i> casualty assessment.</i>

00:52.053 --> 00:55.788
♪♪

00:58.526 --> 01:01.560
[ Helicopter whirring overhead ]

01:01.562 --> 01:03.929
[ Whirring continues ]

01:07.368 --> 01:10.202
Capra: You okay? You okay?
Captain, everyone okay?

01:10.204 --> 01:11.703
-Yeah. Yes.
-Okay, come on.

01:11.705 --> 01:13.505
[ Coughing ]

01:13.507 --> 01:15.407
<i> Pilot: I'm not seeing</i>
<i> any casualties.</i>

01:15.409 --> 01:17.076
<i> There's no one</i>
<i> at the gravesite.</i>

01:17.078 --> 01:20.179
<i> Otherwise, this would've been</i>
<i> a lot worse.</i>

01:20.181 --> 01:21.713
<i> [ Whirring continues ]</i>

01:21.715 --> 01:23.248
Roger that.

01:24.351 --> 01:26.618
[ Coughing continues ]

01:29.857 --> 01:32.624
♪♪

01:52.413 --> 01:54.680
[ Device whirs, beeps ]

01:57.551 --> 01:59.718
[ Beep ]

01:59.720 --> 02:02.121
There's your C-4,
Lieutenant.

02:02.123 --> 02:03.722
♪♪

02:03.724 --> 02:05.791
[ Sighs ]

02:11.966 --> 02:14.900
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

02:14.902 --> 02:17.469
Sharon: We believe
this large flower vase

02:17.471 --> 02:21.473
set beside your father's grave
was the housing for the bomb.

02:21.475 --> 02:24.476
Flynn: And your ex-husband
placed it at the cemetery.

02:24.478 --> 02:27.312
He needed line of sight to see
that we'd found the bomb.

02:27.314 --> 02:30.249
That's why he blew it.
<i> What -- what you're saying</i>
<i> just isn't possible.</i>

02:30.251 --> 02:32.317
<i> Nothing else makes sense.</i>
<i> They may be right.</i>

02:32.319 --> 02:34.620
It was definitely your
ex-husband, ma'am. No question.

02:34.622 --> 02:36.421
How does that make sense?
'Cause it -- it doesn't.

02:36.423 --> 02:40.092
It does if Cristian was
willing to kill a lot of people

02:40.094 --> 02:41.994
to get at<i> you.</i>

02:41.996 --> 02:43.996
But he didn't even know
I was here.

02:45.132 --> 02:47.799
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

02:47.801 --> 02:50.969
Ah, Commander Mason, any news?

02:50.971 --> 02:53.305
My team traced Ortiz through
prison and the military.

02:53.307 --> 02:56.475
No terrorist connections at all.
And no affiliation with MS-13.

02:56.477 --> 02:59.645
-That's not news.
-Well, it is to Winnie Davis.

02:59.647 --> 03:01.180
Liseth:
<i>Oh, my God. Oh, my God.</i>

03:01.182 --> 03:03.315
<i> Wait. Wait. Wait.</i>
<i> Wait a minute.</i>

03:03.317 --> 03:05.817
<i>I wasn't even here when</i>
<i>Cristian was released</i>
<i>from prison.</i>

03:05.819 --> 03:09.121
But he knew exactly
how to bring you back.

03:09.123 --> 03:10.656
That bastard murdered
our father

03:10.658 --> 03:12.858
so he could get Liseth to come
to the funeral?

03:12.860 --> 03:15.294
Is that what you guys
are saying?
It is.

03:15.296 --> 03:18.163
Flynn: Could either of you think
why he'd be so determined

03:18.165 --> 03:20.165
to kill you, Liseth?

03:20.167 --> 03:22.634
<i> Has he threatened you? Did he</i>
<i> call you since his release?</i>

03:22.636 --> 03:24.303
<i> Is there anything</i>
<i> in particular --</i>

03:24.305 --> 03:25.637
<i> How about he's a lunatic?</i>

03:25.639 --> 03:26.872
[ Sniffles ] Not only has he

03:26.874 --> 03:28.840
murdered our father, but he...

03:28.842 --> 03:30.709
[ Inhales deeply ]
He also stabbed my, um...

03:30.711 --> 03:33.312
He stabbed Joseph Euley
to death,

03:33.314 --> 03:36.982
the man with whom you were
having an affair 12 years ago.

03:36.984 --> 03:39.518
Yeah.
Cristian murdered him.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.053
[ Sliding door thuds ]

03:41.055 --> 03:43.055
Sofia: Do you even know
where he is? Cristian?

03:43.057 --> 03:45.824
Sharon: Perhaps you could help
us answer that question, please.

03:45.826 --> 03:48.360
Did your ex-husband have
any particular place

03:48.362 --> 03:49.828
he liked to go?

03:49.830 --> 03:51.997
I don't know. Most of
our marriage, he was --

03:51.999 --> 03:53.865
he was overseas.

03:53.867 --> 03:55.901
But wait a minute. Isn't it<i> your</i>
job to know where Cristian is?

03:55.903 --> 03:57.336
It's not her job.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.904
Flynn: That's what
we're trying to do here.

03:58.906 --> 04:00.739
But maybe you could help us
by giving us a list

04:00.741 --> 04:03.041
of Cristian's old friends

04:03.043 --> 04:05.711
or people he held grudges
against

04:05.713 --> 04:07.813
or people he hated.

04:09.250 --> 04:11.383
Ah, Chief.
We thought you were

04:11.385 --> 04:13.518
at the leadership conference
in Charlotte.
[ Door closes ]

04:13.520 --> 04:15.187
After the cemetery bombing
yesterday,

04:15.189 --> 04:17.022
Chief Pope called me back

04:17.024 --> 04:18.757
and sent Winnie Davis
in my place.

04:18.759 --> 04:21.193
Oh. Are we to read anything
into that?

04:21.195 --> 04:23.061
<i> Flynn: What about the friends?</i>

04:23.063 --> 04:25.264
Maybe you won't be directing
traffic in San Pedro after all.

04:25.266 --> 04:26.732
I'd like to catch up
with this investigation

04:26.734 --> 04:28.567
as soon as possible,
Lieutenant.

04:28.569 --> 04:31.036
Commander, if you're done here,
could I have a word, please?

04:31.038 --> 04:32.704
You need me, Lieutenant,
you know where to find me.

04:32.706 --> 04:35.540
<i> Liseth: He had friends.</i>
<i> They were Marines.</i>

04:35.542 --> 04:37.542
<i> I never even met</i>
<i>any of them more than once.</i>
Buzz...

04:37.544 --> 04:39.611
let the Captain know
we need to regroup.

04:39.613 --> 04:41.713
<i> Liseth: ...mother. I never</i>
<i> even met his father.</i>

04:41.715 --> 04:44.716
Captain, Chief Howard is here
and asking to be briefed.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.718
Hobbs: Our bombing suspect,
Cristian Ortiz,

04:46.720 --> 04:48.954
got a deal for murdering
his wife's boyfriend.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.223
11 years for manslaughter

04:51.225 --> 04:52.958
because his lawyer claimed
self-defense.

04:52.960 --> 04:56.561
It didn't seem likely because
the victim was stabbed 16 times,

04:56.563 --> 04:59.464
and Ortiz obviously brought
the knife with him.

04:59.466 --> 05:01.099
But a jury may have sympathized

05:01.101 --> 05:03.101
with a Marine whose wife
was cheating on him.

05:03.103 --> 05:05.304
According to his cellmate,
Lewis Wilks,

05:05.306 --> 05:08.106
Ortiz claimed his innocence
until the day of his release.

05:08.108 --> 05:12.110
Yes, Wilks also said
that Ortiz blamed his wife

05:12.112 --> 05:13.812
for everything that happened.

05:13.814 --> 05:16.248
-Ex-wife, sir.
-Technicality.

05:16.250 --> 05:18.150
And Ortiz left a bomb behind
in her father's house.

05:18.152 --> 05:20.919
-Maybe to blow her up.
-The bomb was marked with blood

05:20.921 --> 05:23.488
that couldn't have been there
from the gunshot wound.

05:23.490 --> 05:25.924
Why leave a bomb behind
to kill your wife,

05:25.926 --> 05:27.326
and then do stuff to it

05:27.328 --> 05:29.127
that means we have to collect it
as evidence?

05:29.129 --> 05:31.997
That, Chief, is the question
that's troubling all of us.

05:31.999 --> 05:34.433
I'm more bothered
by all this missing C-4.

05:34.435 --> 05:36.835
Let's go back
to this manslaughter charge

05:36.837 --> 05:38.437
for a moment.

05:38.439 --> 05:40.439
Was Ortiz definitively guilty?

05:40.441 --> 05:42.007
He took a plea bargain.

05:42.009 --> 05:44.109
We had a voicemail where
he threatened Euley.

05:44.111 --> 05:47.112
And his connection to the
murder weapon was irrefutable --

05:47.114 --> 05:50.849
a Marine-issue KA-BAR knife
covered with his prints and DNA

05:50.851 --> 05:53.118
and Mr. Euley's blood residue
on the blade.

05:53.120 --> 05:56.455
Julio, ask Dr. Morales to
put together the autopsy report

05:56.457 --> 05:58.290
from Mr. Euley's death.

05:58.292 --> 05:59.791
Okay, I don't know
how to explain the radio,

05:59.793 --> 06:01.626
but Ortiz could've wrapped
something

06:01.628 --> 06:04.196
around the hilt of the knife,
like a plastic bag.

06:04.198 --> 06:07.466
If he was being that careful,
why not wipe the blade after?

06:07.468 --> 06:09.668
And the hilt. Instead of leaving
his fingerprints on it.

06:09.670 --> 06:14.206
All right, don't forget
Lewis Wilks, Ortiz's cellmate,

06:14.208 --> 06:17.476
indicated to us that he had
more to tell us.

06:17.478 --> 06:19.044
But he won't talk
without a deal.

06:19.046 --> 06:22.514
Wilks has six years left
on a drug sentence.

06:22.516 --> 06:25.050
And those six years
aren't going away

06:25.052 --> 06:27.819
without information necessary
to find and convict Ortiz --

06:27.821 --> 06:30.055
I'm not worried
about a conviction, Andrea.

06:30.057 --> 06:32.391
There are pounds,
<i> pounds</i> of C-4 unaccounted for.

06:32.393 --> 06:34.159
He's obviously
willing to use it.

06:34.161 --> 06:35.727
I want this guy in custody.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.997
We may have the conviction part
locked up.

06:38.999 --> 06:41.166
I found a partial print

06:41.168 --> 06:43.835
on the interior
of the ceramic vase

06:43.837 --> 06:46.338
that housed our cemetery bomb.

06:46.340 --> 06:49.074
Does the partial belong
to Ortiz?

06:49.076 --> 06:51.510
-Let's take a look.
-I'll check with my boss.

06:51.512 --> 06:54.012
But Wilks' information
has to be good!

06:54.014 --> 06:56.681
We will make sure he knows that!

06:56.683 --> 06:59.050
Uh, Mom?

06:59.052 --> 07:01.253
She talks tough,
but she's already drawn up

07:01.255 --> 07:03.755
the paperwork reducing the guy's
sentence by three years.

07:03.757 --> 07:06.591
Just so you know.

07:09.696 --> 07:11.730
Hey, Provenza.

07:11.732 --> 07:13.532
I've been doing some thinking.

07:13.534 --> 07:16.868
-Are you in pain?
-No, I -- Oh, very funny.

07:16.870 --> 07:20.539
N-no, I figure since my health
has been pretty much on track --

07:20.541 --> 07:24.943
I'm eating better,
I'm exercising, vitamins...

07:24.945 --> 07:29.781
So how long before I...
I-I'm back in the field?

07:29.783 --> 07:34.719
Flynn, you have had
two big health scares in a row.

07:34.721 --> 07:38.957
Now, getting you
off of desk duty

07:38.959 --> 07:42.427
creates huge
liability issues here.

07:42.429 --> 07:44.729
And returning to the field?

07:44.731 --> 07:47.299
Well...

07:47.301 --> 07:52.103
You need the right person to
be promoted to Assistant Chief.

07:52.105 --> 07:55.307
♪♪

07:55.309 --> 07:57.576
[ Computer beeps ]
<i> Automated female voice:</i>
<i> Match found.</i>

07:57.578 --> 08:00.579
He's in the system,
but he's not Cristian Ortiz.

08:00.581 --> 08:02.414
Buzz?

08:02.416 --> 08:04.816
Partial on the vase belongs
to Franklin Dwayne Pearl,

08:04.818 --> 08:07.586
arrested in 2009
for armed robbery,

08:07.588 --> 08:09.154
released on parole
six months ago.

08:09.156 --> 08:11.156
Nolan: Looks like he hasn't
got in any trouble since.

08:11.158 --> 08:12.924
He's made every parole hearing.

08:12.926 --> 08:15.494
Well, it's what he's been doing
between parole hearings

08:15.496 --> 08:17.429
that we're worried about,
Nolan.

08:17.431 --> 08:19.598
Sharon: Where is Mr. Pearl
right now?

08:19.600 --> 08:21.933
Uh, looks like he lives...
here.

08:21.935 --> 08:24.769
And works at
Second Shot Thrift,

08:24.771 --> 08:26.505
right around the corner
from his apartment.

08:26.507 --> 08:28.807
Sharon: Let's see
if this guy's at work

08:28.809 --> 08:31.843
and then see what he has
been working on.

08:37.351 --> 08:39.117
I'm not going anywhere,
in spite of Napa being, like,

08:39.119 --> 08:40.819
the best job I can get
right now.
But I... [ Groans ]

08:40.821 --> 08:44.523
[ Inhales deeply ] I can't
believe I'm saying this. I...

08:44.525 --> 08:48.660
Napa's great, and I totally get
what it means to you.

08:48.662 --> 08:51.463
But what about us?

08:51.465 --> 08:54.332
Well, this is not
a "What about us?" thing.

08:54.334 --> 08:56.668
Because "us" could be
living in Napa.

08:56.670 --> 08:58.470
"Us" could be living
in Oakland.

08:58.472 --> 09:01.172
This is an "all about you
wanting to stay here" thing.

09:01.174 --> 09:05.143
Okay, no, I-I looked into
transferring to Berkeley, okay?

09:05.145 --> 09:07.012
I-I have the grades.

09:07.014 --> 09:10.649
But I'm on track to graduate
from UCLA next December, okay?

09:10.651 --> 09:12.717
Berkeley does semesters
instead of quarters.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.986
That would add
an extra six months to my --

09:14.988 --> 09:17.656
Yeah, and Napa would add
an extra $15,000 to my paycheck.

09:17.658 --> 09:19.991
But that's not what matters.
Hold -- hold on, Gus. Okay?

09:19.993 --> 09:21.326
Can you just hold on for --
No. No.

09:21.328 --> 09:23.395
I already said that
I'm not going.

09:23.397 --> 09:26.731
But let's both be clear that
we are staying here in L.A.

09:26.733 --> 09:29.334
You are not applying to
law schools in other cities.

09:29.336 --> 09:32.671
And if you don't get into
one around here, that's it.

09:32.673 --> 09:35.073
And meanwhile,
I'll just keep working

09:35.075 --> 09:37.208
my stupid, not very important
restaurant job,

09:37.210 --> 09:40.078
because this is where
we live. Period.
Gus, Gus,

09:40.080 --> 09:42.380
I don't think
that your job is stupid.

09:42.382 --> 09:45.717
In fact, it's -- it's such
a big promotion that

09:45.719 --> 09:49.254
I-I was just surprised
that your boss gave it to you.

09:49.256 --> 09:51.022
Just because it's
so incredibly important.

09:51.024 --> 09:53.258
Yeah, it's just not as important
as the things that you wanna do.

09:53.260 --> 09:54.859
I mean, how could
being a sous-chef

09:54.861 --> 09:57.095
compete with being a lawyer
or -- or a journalist

09:57.097 --> 09:59.331
or anything else Rusty Beck
decides to do with his life?

10:04.071 --> 10:06.438
I'm covering for someone
during prep tomorrow.

10:06.440 --> 10:08.740
I gotta be at work early.

10:08.742 --> 10:11.109
You can come by around 9:00
and pick me up.

10:12.546 --> 10:14.679
I'm just -- I'm going home.

10:16.883 --> 10:19.284
[ Door closes ]

10:19.286 --> 10:20.885
[ Sighs deeply ]

10:20.887 --> 10:22.721
Tao: Remember,
don't unnerve the guy.

10:22.723 --> 10:25.657
Just shop until you find him.

10:27.294 --> 10:30.795
<i> ♪♪</i>

10:32.399 --> 10:35.800
Woman:<i> ♪ I wonder ♪</i>

10:35.802 --> 10:39.437
<i> ♪ What you think ♪</i>

10:39.439 --> 10:42.273
<i> ♪ When I was down and out ♪</i>

10:42.275 --> 10:45.577
Holy crap. Julio.

10:45.579 --> 10:49.080
The radio used to house the bomb
we found in Albert Luna's house.

10:49.082 --> 10:52.417
-We're in the right place.
-Mm-hmm.

10:52.419 --> 10:55.320
<i> ♪♪</i>

10:57.491 --> 10:58.890
I see him.

11:03.430 --> 11:05.830
Oh, my God.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.603
[ Clears throat ] Excuse me.

11:11.605 --> 11:13.772
Uh, sir, can you tell me
how much this is?

11:13.774 --> 11:16.808
-Sure.
-Yeah, there's no, um, price.

11:16.810 --> 11:18.343
[ Sykes speaks indistinctly ]

11:18.345 --> 11:21.146
Huh. Right.
I'll be right back.
Yeah.

11:21.148 --> 11:23.515
Pearl: [ Grunts ]
What the hell?

11:23.517 --> 11:25.450
Got him. Bring in the dogs.
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

11:25.452 --> 11:28.119
-[ Groans ] What the hell, man?!
-Where's Cristian Ortiz?

11:28.121 --> 11:29.954
Who? I-I don't know.

11:29.956 --> 11:31.823
I don't know any Cristian
whatever his name is. [ Groans ]

11:31.825 --> 11:33.458
You are in enough trouble
already!
[ Siren wailing ]

11:33.460 --> 11:35.160
We know you are connected
to Ortiz.

11:35.162 --> 11:36.795
-Tell where he is right now...
-I don't know any Ortiz.

11:36.797 --> 11:38.296
...or you're going back
to prison today

11:38.298 --> 11:39.864
until we can charge you
for murder!

11:39.866 --> 11:41.466
We know Ortiz was
in this store.

11:41.468 --> 11:43.034
He had merchandise you sold him.

11:43.036 --> 11:45.136
Oh, no, no, no, man.
I never met no Ortiz.

11:45.138 --> 11:47.639
Your fingerprints were found
on a vase,

11:47.641 --> 11:50.542
just like this one that Ortiz
used to blow up a cemetery!

11:50.544 --> 11:52.343
Whoa! Whoa! My fingerprints

11:52.345 --> 11:54.045
are on shelves full of shit
like that!

11:54.047 --> 11:55.980
You're saying you never saw
this guy? Is that it?

11:55.982 --> 11:59.984
I don't know. I...
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:59.986 --> 12:02.320
Maybe the dude
came in here some.

12:02.322 --> 12:03.688
But if he did, he had a beard.

12:03.690 --> 12:05.523
Oh. Oh, see, now you remember.

12:05.525 --> 12:07.492
Amazing.
No, seriously, man.

12:07.494 --> 12:09.227
If it's the same dude, he was
in here a couple of weeks ago.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.995
-He bought a boatload of stuff.
-Like what?

12:10.997 --> 12:13.331
[ Sighs ] Like that.

12:13.333 --> 12:17.335
Sharon: Cristian Ortiz
purchased items like these

12:17.337 --> 12:20.338
at a thrift store
in North Hollywood.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.407
Why?
That depends.

12:22.409 --> 12:24.175
Depends on what?

12:24.177 --> 12:26.211
That depends on what you're
willing to offer Mr. Wilks

12:26.213 --> 12:27.679
in return for his information.

12:27.681 --> 12:30.682
Your client has six years left
on his sentence.

12:30.684 --> 12:32.250
Mm-hmm.
We're willing to cut that
to three,

12:32.252 --> 12:35.019
if what he tells us
is actually worth anything.

12:35.021 --> 12:37.021
What? Three? No, no, no.

12:37.023 --> 12:39.591
[ Chuckles ] No, are --
are you kidding me?<i> Three?</i>

12:39.593 --> 12:41.359
I'm sorry, guys. You gotta
do better than that.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.695
Mr. Wilks' help could save
maybe hundreds of lives here.

12:43.697 --> 12:45.697
Or we could end up catching
Ortiz on the street,

12:45.699 --> 12:48.533
and we see Wilks
sometime next decade.

12:48.535 --> 12:51.069
Six years or three. That's it.

12:51.071 --> 12:53.271
Take it or regret it.

12:53.273 --> 12:56.608
♪♪

12:56.610 --> 12:58.409
[ Pen clatters ]

12:58.411 --> 12:59.911
[ Sighs deeply ]

12:59.913 --> 13:02.447
Son of a bitch. Fine. Fine.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.716
May I?

13:04.718 --> 13:08.319
[ Sighs ]

13:10.423 --> 13:12.490
[ Groans ]

13:14.227 --> 13:16.795
You -- you see
all these hollow parts?

13:16.797 --> 13:18.429
They're called voids.
All right?

13:18.431 --> 13:20.732
Empty spaces where
something can be hidden.

13:20.734 --> 13:23.902
<i> Everything</i> here has a void.

13:23.904 --> 13:26.104
I would use these items...Hmm?

13:26.106 --> 13:28.573
To hide drugs.

13:28.575 --> 13:30.542
Ortiz...

13:32.312 --> 13:34.112
He's using them for explosives.

13:34.114 --> 13:36.815
So everything he bought has
the potential to become a bomb.

13:36.817 --> 13:39.784
Housed in ordinary items...
<i>Wilks: I think that's the idea.</i>

13:39.786 --> 13:41.753
...that wouldn't be checked
for explosives.

13:41.755 --> 13:43.254
And if Ortiz bought as much

13:43.256 --> 13:44.989
as the guy at
the thrift store said...

13:44.991 --> 13:46.591
He could have dozens
of bombs.

13:46.593 --> 13:49.260
But where are they?
And what are they all for?

13:49.262 --> 13:52.263
Right. Ortiz needed
one bomb to off the ex

13:52.265 --> 13:54.265
and one to off her family, too.

13:54.267 --> 13:56.301
And then the others are
for what?

13:56.303 --> 13:57.635
<i> Sharon: Don't worry.</i>

13:57.637 --> 14:00.338
Ortiz said
his ex-wife framed him.

14:00.340 --> 14:02.440
She killed Euley, not him.

14:02.442 --> 14:05.109
That's not what Ortiz said
when he accepted his sentence.

14:05.111 --> 14:07.946
Look, the guy spent, like,
100% of his time on the inside

14:07.948 --> 14:09.848
researching his case,
and he found details

14:09.850 --> 14:11.649
that you guys didn't think
to hunt for.

14:11.651 --> 14:15.119
Before, you said you didn't
believe that Ortiz was innocent.

14:15.121 --> 14:17.121
Ah, well...

14:17.123 --> 14:18.857
How am I gonna tell you
his wife killed Euley

14:18.859 --> 14:20.191
and still get my deal?

14:20.193 --> 14:21.993
You don't know Cristian
is innocent.

14:21.995 --> 14:24.162
I know Euley's mother wrote
Cristian in prison,

14:24.164 --> 14:26.030
asking why he killed her son

14:26.032 --> 14:28.967
a week after Euley broke it off
with Liseth.

14:28.969 --> 14:30.535
And Ortiz said his wife was

14:30.537 --> 14:32.470
the only other person
who had access

14:32.472 --> 14:34.505
to all that stuff he brought
home from the military,

14:34.507 --> 14:37.141
including his knife.

14:37.143 --> 14:38.810
So she got rid of her boyfriend,

14:38.812 --> 14:40.311
who had the nerve to break up
with her,

14:40.313 --> 14:43.047
and her husband
at the same time.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.818
But that's not
the biggest news here.

14:46.820 --> 14:49.153
Ortiz didn't just blame
his ex-wife for all that.

14:49.155 --> 14:51.022
Ye Gods.

14:51.024 --> 14:52.724
<i> He blamed you guys.</i>

14:53.827 --> 14:55.660
Who do you mean by "you guys"?

14:55.662 --> 14:58.229
The LAPD.

14:58.231 --> 15:00.865
Cristian's lawyers told him even
though he might be innocent,

15:00.867 --> 15:03.001
LAPD had enough
physical evidence

15:03.003 --> 15:04.669
to put him away
for the rest of his life.

15:04.671 --> 15:08.506
Hobbs: Manslaughter is a good
deal for murder... [ Sighs ]

15:08.508 --> 15:09.908
<i> unless you didn't do it.</i>

15:09.910 --> 15:11.676
<i> Sanchez:</i>
<i> Take away somebody's future,</i>

15:11.678 --> 15:13.745
<i> and they could stay angry</i>
<i> for a very long time.</i>

15:13.747 --> 15:17.849
So Cristian blames Liseth,
and he blames us.

15:17.851 --> 15:21.352
He wants to get revenge
on the bitch, sure.

15:21.354 --> 15:24.355
But also wants to take down
the system that helped her.

15:24.357 --> 15:25.556
[ Pen clatters ]

15:25.558 --> 15:27.258
I didn't do the autopsy,

15:27.260 --> 15:29.928
and knowing what we do now,
I have issues.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.529
What sort of issues?

15:31.531 --> 15:33.865
We know that the murder weapon
is consistent

15:33.867 --> 15:36.034
with the weapon Ortiz kept
from his time in the service.

15:36.036 --> 15:38.236
-A KA-BAR Marine knife.
-Correct.

15:38.238 --> 15:41.205
Serrated blade on one side,
razor-sharp on the other.

15:41.207 --> 15:43.908
And we know
that the initial attack

15:43.910 --> 15:45.576
was a downward stab

15:45.578 --> 15:47.946
into the soft tissue
of the victim's neck.

15:47.948 --> 15:51.382
The blade went all the way
into the hilt.

15:51.384 --> 15:55.553
And from the angle, we know that
the attack came from behind.

15:55.555 --> 15:57.922
The rest of the 16 stab wounds

15:57.924 --> 16:00.558
were to the victim's chest,
straight in.

16:00.560 --> 16:03.261
Means Euley probably collapsed
and was stabbed from above.

16:03.263 --> 16:05.229
That's exactly right,
Detective Nolan.

16:05.231 --> 16:06.597
Very good!

16:06.599 --> 16:08.933
But there's one more thing.

16:08.935 --> 16:12.136
The chest wounds were
haphazardly inflicted.

16:12.138 --> 16:13.905
Sloppy. Lacking in depth.

16:13.907 --> 16:15.740
Not the work
of a trained Marine.

16:15.742 --> 16:17.976
And shallow for a guy
the size of Ortiz.

16:17.978 --> 16:20.645
-Very shallow.
-But wouldn't Ortiz's attorney

16:20.647 --> 16:22.814
been all over this information?

16:22.816 --> 16:25.917
I'm sure, if his public defender
had ever received it.

16:25.919 --> 16:29.921
But the Statement of Facts was
completed based on the prelim.

16:29.923 --> 16:33.658
The full autopsy report
took 62 days to complete.

16:33.660 --> 16:35.660
And Ortiz made his deal
in 30.

16:35.662 --> 16:39.630
Based on false assumptions.
Okay.

16:39.632 --> 16:42.433
What do we actually know here?

16:42.435 --> 16:46.170
Ortiz spent 11 years in a cell
claiming his innocence.

16:46.172 --> 16:49.140
Whatever he did then,
he's blowing stuff up now.

16:49.142 --> 16:51.809
And he's definitely trying
to kill his ex-wife.

16:51.811 --> 16:53.111
And don't forget the whole

16:53.113 --> 16:54.779
"taking down the system"
thing, too.

16:54.781 --> 16:57.982
Or the ordinary items
in which Ortiz is hiding bombs.

16:57.984 --> 17:00.618
I think maybe his ex-wife
should stay with us

17:00.620 --> 17:02.120
just a little longer.

17:02.122 --> 17:04.489
You know, to ensure her safety.

17:04.491 --> 17:06.824
Flynn: Yeah. Maybe Liseth
could be scared into --

17:06.826 --> 17:08.459
I mean, frightened enough --

17:08.461 --> 17:10.962
to tell us where her husband's
knife was stored.

17:10.964 --> 17:12.463
We could bring her
a change of clothes

17:12.465 --> 17:14.332
and stuff to make her feel
more comfortable.

17:14.334 --> 17:15.967
That's a good place to start.

17:15.969 --> 17:18.202
Let's get patrol
to stop by her dad's house

17:18.204 --> 17:20.304
and pick up her things.

17:20.306 --> 17:23.875
Meanwhile, I want to go over
every LAPD incident report

17:23.877 --> 17:25.376
since Cristian started

17:25.378 --> 17:29.180
on his little thrift-store
shopping spree.

17:29.182 --> 17:33.184
I think it is possible
that the rest of the LAPD

17:33.186 --> 17:37.021
has been operating under
false assumptions, as well.

17:37.023 --> 17:39.924
♪♪

17:44.831 --> 17:46.464
[ Police radio chatter ]

17:50.503 --> 17:54.572
♪♪

18:11.524 --> 18:13.057
[ Buzzer ]

18:13.059 --> 18:16.360
♪♪

18:16.362 --> 18:18.096
[ Door closes ]

18:26.372 --> 18:27.872
[ Door opens ]

18:27.874 --> 18:29.707
♪♪

18:29.709 --> 18:31.375
What is this?
You telling me I can't go home?

18:31.377 --> 18:33.711
Don't I have a right to leave?
Well, yes, certainly.

18:33.713 --> 18:37.548
[ Door closes ]
We -- we just wanna keep you
safe while your ex is at large.

18:37.550 --> 18:39.417
[ Scoffs ] So what am I
supposed to do,

18:39.419 --> 18:41.219
stay here until
you catch Cristian?

18:41.221 --> 18:42.887
Is that why you brought me
my things?

18:42.889 --> 18:44.288
Because I'm living here now?

18:44.290 --> 18:45.723
What if you never catch him?
What then?

18:45.725 --> 18:48.059
In an effort to locate
your ex-husband,

18:48.061 --> 18:50.461
we've gone over everything
from Joseph Euley's death

18:50.463 --> 18:53.464
again and again, looking for
something we missed.

18:53.466 --> 18:55.433
And there's just one thing.
What's that?

18:55.435 --> 18:57.468
Where your husband
kept the knife he used

18:57.470 --> 18:59.303
to stab your boyfriend to death.

18:59.305 --> 19:02.607
Now back then,
you told the police

19:02.609 --> 19:06.611
that this knife absolutely
did not come from your home.

19:06.613 --> 19:08.479
Yeah. So what?

19:08.481 --> 19:10.915
12 years is a long time
to remember something you said.

19:10.917 --> 19:13.251
Especially if it wasn't
the truth.

19:13.253 --> 19:15.586
Provenza:<i> Please, have a seat.</i>
<i> We were wondering</i>

19:15.588 --> 19:18.156
<i> where else this knife</i>
<i> could have been hidden.</i>

19:18.158 --> 19:20.925
<i> Why on Earth would that</i>
<i> be important now?</i>

19:20.927 --> 19:23.094
Because if we knew
where your ex kept the knife,

19:23.096 --> 19:26.097
he might've been keeping other
stuff he stole from the Marines.

19:26.099 --> 19:29.100
Provenza:<i> Yes, like</i>
<i> the C-4 explosives</i>

19:29.102 --> 19:32.803
<i> that he used to try and murder</i>
<i> you and your family.</i>

19:32.805 --> 19:36.174
<i> And he has more of</i>
<i> those explosives. A lot more.</i>

19:36.176 --> 19:38.609
Now we'll see how scared
she really is.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.312
<i> If we knew where the knife</i>
<i> came from, we believe</i>

19:41.314 --> 19:44.315
the rest of the C-4
may be there, as well.

19:44.317 --> 19:46.484
And maybe even Cristian,
too.

19:46.486 --> 19:48.152
Really? Are you sure?

19:48.154 --> 19:50.121
Well, it's our best hope.

19:50.123 --> 19:53.324
So if you have<i> any</i> suspicion

19:53.326 --> 19:57.228
of where your ex-husband
kept this knife...

19:58.831 --> 20:02.466
Cristian had a storage unit
that he used

20:02.468 --> 20:05.303
<i> to keep all the things</i>
<i>that he stole from the Marines.</i>

20:05.305 --> 20:07.371
<i> He used to call it</i>
<i> his "barracks."</i>

20:07.373 --> 20:10.541
<i>He would go there all the time.</i>
<i> I don't know why, but...</i>

20:10.543 --> 20:14.145
Well, thank you.
Thank you, ma'am.

20:14.147 --> 20:18.349
Now, this is
very, very important.

20:18.351 --> 20:22.820
Do you recall where this
storage facility is located?

20:22.822 --> 20:26.557
Um, could you write down
the name, the address,

20:26.559 --> 20:29.694
and the number of
the storage unit itself?

20:29.696 --> 20:31.329
[ Pen clicks ]

20:31.331 --> 20:33.497
[ Sighs ]

20:33.499 --> 20:35.066
<i> [ Pen scribbling ]</i>

20:35.068 --> 20:38.035
<i> He doesn't just have knives</i>
<i> or explosives.</i>

20:38.037 --> 20:41.038
He has guns.

20:41.040 --> 20:44.041
And that's the beginning
of her written confession.

20:44.043 --> 20:46.010
How is that a confession?

20:46.012 --> 20:48.379
Because she just admitted
to knowing where the knife was,

20:48.381 --> 20:50.848
and now she's describing
everything that was there.

20:50.850 --> 20:52.583
Nolan: It's gonna be hard
to convict her of Euley's murder

20:52.585 --> 20:54.518
without her husband's statement.

20:54.520 --> 20:57.588
And it doesn't get him off the
hook for murdering her father.

20:57.590 --> 20:59.857
Or the attempt on 50 people
at the funeral.

20:59.859 --> 21:03.027
But now we might just know
where he is.

21:03.029 --> 21:05.596
This could all be over
very quickly.

21:06.933 --> 21:09.200
Mike, where are we going?

21:09.202 --> 21:12.103
♪♪

21:17.877 --> 21:19.944
Inside. Inside.
Watch your head.

21:21.447 --> 21:25.483
♪♪

21:28.621 --> 21:31.555
Ortiz is making bombs
out of everything,

21:31.557 --> 21:33.391
and he's got a lot of C-4 left.

21:33.393 --> 21:35.893
If there's a bomb, the dog will
smell it, I promise.

21:35.895 --> 21:38.729
Also, maintain complete
radio discipline.

21:38.731 --> 21:40.564
Good luck, people.

21:40.566 --> 21:43.501
Now let's work this dog.
This way. This way.

21:45.271 --> 21:47.004
[ Knocks on window ]

21:50.076 --> 21:53.277
We've confirmed that Ortiz
is renting space 108,

21:53.279 --> 21:55.313
just like his ex-wife
told us.

21:55.315 --> 21:57.748
Now if he is there...
We'll be ready.

21:57.750 --> 21:59.483
SIS has established a perimeter.
[ Police radio chatter ]

21:59.485 --> 22:02.119
SWAT has elevated positions
on buildings north and east.

22:02.121 --> 22:05.489
Nah, if Ortiz tries to escape,
he won't get far.

22:05.491 --> 22:06.924
Thanks. Thanks, Chief.

22:06.926 --> 22:08.459
I'm telling you, Chief,
I'm more worried

22:08.461 --> 22:10.294
about what he may have
left behind.

22:10.296 --> 22:12.763
Capra's being followed in
by the rest of the Bomb Squad

22:12.765 --> 22:16.100
and thermal imaging
to assess the storage unit.

22:16.102 --> 22:19.670
No, if Mr. Ortiz planted
something special for us,

22:19.672 --> 22:21.205
we'll soon know.

22:25.111 --> 22:26.677
[ Camera turns on ]

22:26.679 --> 22:29.513
♪♪

22:33.319 --> 22:36.187
Buzz, thermal imaging online.

22:41.027 --> 22:44.662
Uh, doesn't look like much.

22:44.664 --> 22:46.664
Doesn't have to.
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

22:46.666 --> 22:50.468
But he<i> was</i> living here.
We missed him. Damn it.

22:50.470 --> 22:51.802
[ Vibrates ]

22:51.804 --> 22:53.637
Capra, I'm putting you
on speaker.

22:53.639 --> 22:55.172
[ Cellphone beeps ]

22:55.174 --> 22:56.707
Captain, looks like
we're all clear.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.376
Okay, Lieutenant,
give it a go.

23:00.146 --> 23:03.047
Tao:
Bomb Squad's ready to breach.

23:05.184 --> 23:07.718
[ Door rattles ]

23:07.720 --> 23:12.556
♪♪

23:12.558 --> 23:15.059
[ Device beeping ]

23:18.664 --> 23:21.165
[ Beeping continues ]

23:21.167 --> 23:24.235
♪♪

23:25.538 --> 23:30.241
[ Beeping continues ]

23:33.513 --> 23:35.613
Negative. We're clear.

23:36.883 --> 23:38.582
Heading in now.

23:38.584 --> 23:41.419
♪♪

23:52.865 --> 23:55.266
Check this out.

24:00.406 --> 24:02.373
"I was innocent."

24:02.375 --> 24:03.808
Not anymore.

24:05.378 --> 24:07.378
This guy does not
know subtle, does he?

24:07.380 --> 24:10.014
No, but he knows us.

24:13.286 --> 24:16.020
♪♪

24:19.058 --> 24:22.226
Tao: No sign of any of his
thrift-store purchases.

24:22.228 --> 24:25.463
I think I know why.

24:27.934 --> 24:30.401
Holy crap.

24:30.403 --> 24:33.404
Captain, we got a bunch
of empty cellphone shells.

24:33.406 --> 24:36.073
We see it, Lieutenant.
We see it.

24:36.075 --> 24:38.909
If Ortiz has torn apart
that many cellphones,

24:38.911 --> 24:41.111
he's probably constructed
a lot more bombs.

24:41.113 --> 24:42.813
But where are they?

24:42.815 --> 24:45.082
I don't think we have very much
time to figure that out.

24:45.084 --> 24:47.451
♪♪

24:53.092 --> 24:55.092
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

24:55.094 --> 24:56.460
Yes?

24:56.462 --> 24:59.930
Hey. Uh, I'm Rusty.
I'm Gus' --

24:59.932 --> 25:03.100
Rusty. Yes. It's nice to put
a face to the name.

25:03.102 --> 25:05.135
I'm Aiden Reed.
Oh.

25:05.137 --> 25:07.304
Gus told me so much about you.
I'm glad you're here.

25:07.306 --> 25:09.473
Yeah. It's -- it's good
to meet you, too.

25:09.475 --> 25:11.175
And, um, thank you, Aiden.

25:11.177 --> 25:15.446
Thank you so much
just for all the --

25:15.448 --> 25:17.281
the great things
that you've done for Gus.

25:17.283 --> 25:19.984
We --
we really appreciate it.

25:19.986 --> 25:21.619
Is he here or...?
No.

25:21.621 --> 25:23.120
Uh, when I heard
you were coming by,

25:23.122 --> 25:25.122
I sent him on a run with Chef
to the fish market.

25:25.124 --> 25:27.458
He was torn,
but you know Gus, right?

25:27.460 --> 25:29.860
He always wants to go
the extra mile.
Right.

25:29.862 --> 25:31.629
It's one of the reasons
I was a bit disappointed

25:31.631 --> 25:33.998
that he turned down
this Napa opportunity.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.799
But what can I do?

25:35.801 --> 25:37.368
Gus can't see what's
in his best interest

25:37.370 --> 25:39.003
'cause he's in a relationship

25:39.005 --> 25:41.572
with a really, really
insecure college student.

25:45.311 --> 25:47.144
Does that come up a lot?

25:47.146 --> 25:50.314
Gus saying no to you because
he's already in a relationship.

25:50.316 --> 25:53.684
Have you -- have you been
turned down before?

25:53.686 --> 25:55.653
More like turned away.

25:55.655 --> 25:59.323
But, yeah, he won't take me up
on dinners out or drinks.

25:59.325 --> 26:01.325
But I'm guessing that's
because of everything

26:01.327 --> 26:03.360
you did for his sister.

26:03.362 --> 26:05.896
Why else let a needy boy
like you call all the shots

26:05.898 --> 26:07.531
when he could be doing
so much better?

26:07.533 --> 26:09.533
Oh, like being with you?

26:09.535 --> 26:11.502
That's why you're promoting him
to Napa, isn't it?

26:11.504 --> 26:13.070
Instead of here?

26:13.072 --> 26:15.172
Or did the two-star
Michelin chef that you hired

26:15.174 --> 26:16.707
just refuse
to enter his kitchen

26:16.709 --> 26:19.176
unless Gus was there
as his new right hand?

26:19.178 --> 26:21.912
Are you really upset with me,
or -- or because you --

26:21.914 --> 26:24.682
you found someone
that you can't buy?

26:24.684 --> 26:26.083
Well...

26:27.920 --> 26:30.154
I hear you know
all about that.

26:32.358 --> 26:34.425
Hey, why don't you tell Gus

26:34.427 --> 26:38.395
that it's not all his hard work
or talent that I'm rewarding?

26:38.397 --> 26:40.064
That his promotions are

26:40.066 --> 26:41.765
just because I'm physically
attracted to him.

26:41.767 --> 26:43.701
Please tell him that.

26:43.703 --> 26:47.371
And if you won't, consider how
Gus'll be constantly weighing

26:47.373 --> 26:50.674
what he sacrificed to hang
around here while you grow up.

26:51.911 --> 26:53.877
You think you're done
making mistakes?

26:53.879 --> 26:56.547
Oh, I'm pretty sure I could
wait you out.

26:56.549 --> 26:59.550
Speaking of which, I think
Gus will be back any minute.

26:59.552 --> 27:02.286
So, uh, please have a seat.
Have some coffee.

27:02.288 --> 27:03.854
It's on the house.

27:08.127 --> 27:10.561
Flynn: In addition to the bombs
that have already went off,

27:10.563 --> 27:12.896
these cellphone shells
are an indication

27:12.898 --> 27:15.633
that there's at least
20 explosive devices

27:15.635 --> 27:17.601
planted somewhere around
the city.

27:17.603 --> 27:20.270
-But where?
-Doesn't Cristian's target,

27:20.272 --> 27:23.574
combined with what we know
about the first bomb,

27:23.576 --> 27:25.109
indicate the pattern?

27:25.111 --> 27:27.077
There was blood on the radio
and under it,

27:27.079 --> 27:30.080
meaning it was<i> meant</i>
to be collected as evidence.

27:30.082 --> 27:32.916
If we had booked it, that radio
would have ended up

27:32.918 --> 27:35.085
in one of our evidence lockers.

27:35.087 --> 27:37.154
It should've been brought here,
where we would have kept it

27:37.156 --> 27:38.756
until we tried the murderer.

27:38.758 --> 27:41.258
Yes. He blames his wife
for what happened to him,

27:41.260 --> 27:42.993
but he also blames us.

27:42.995 --> 27:44.762
Sykes: And the fact that we had
physical evidence,

27:44.764 --> 27:47.498
which turned out to be
less than it seemed.

27:47.500 --> 27:49.433
Oh, my God.

27:49.435 --> 27:51.769
There are 21 LAPD divisions.

27:51.771 --> 27:54.605
That's 21 evidence lockers,
plus the bomb at the cemetery.

27:54.607 --> 27:56.173
That's our 22 cellphones.

27:56.175 --> 27:58.108
Flynn: He doesn't just want
revenge on his wife.

27:58.110 --> 28:00.444
He wants to screw
the entire LAPD, too,

28:00.446 --> 28:02.312
the way we screwed him.

28:02.314 --> 28:05.182
I know the justice system might
not be always fair to everyone,

28:05.184 --> 28:07.151
but if he'd only given us
a chance --

28:07.153 --> 28:10.120
We could have made it
all better?

28:10.122 --> 28:13.957
Buzz, look, I know it's hard
to accept,

28:13.959 --> 28:15.793
but not everybody wants
our help.

28:15.795 --> 28:17.494
How are we supposed
to locate every bomb

28:17.496 --> 28:19.029
in every evidence locker

28:19.031 --> 28:21.131
when Ortiz could detonate
any of them any second?

28:21.133 --> 28:23.801
We may have a solution for that.
Buzz, give me a hand, please.

28:23.803 --> 28:27.805
♪♪

28:27.807 --> 28:29.807
Buzz: Each of the cellphone
shells found in Mr. Ortiz's

28:29.809 --> 28:33.711
storage locker has a lot number
for quality control and recalls.

28:33.713 --> 28:36.013
But in this situation,
we can translate

28:36.015 --> 28:38.682
each of the serial numbers
from the cell casings

28:38.684 --> 28:40.150
into actual phone numbers.

28:40.152 --> 28:41.518
And by knowing
all the phone numbers...

28:41.520 --> 28:42.986
Sharon:
We can block each cellphone.

28:42.988 --> 28:44.888
Well, that will make them
pretty much useless

28:44.890 --> 28:47.524
as detonation devices.
How long will it take?

28:47.526 --> 28:51.328
Uh, 20 cellphones? Not long.
I'll go as fast as I can.

28:51.330 --> 28:54.565
Also, we need to evacuate
every evidence facility

28:54.567 --> 28:56.500
at every division in the LAPD.

28:56.502 --> 28:58.335
-Sykes: We're on it.
-Nolan: Yes, Ma'am. Right away.

28:58.337 --> 28:59.837
One other thing.
By knowing all the phone numbers

28:59.839 --> 29:01.538
from Cristian's detonators,
we can check

29:01.540 --> 29:03.340
all the incoming calls.
And there's only one,

29:03.342 --> 29:05.509
because the C-4 in the radio
was detonated by accident.

29:05.511 --> 29:08.011
But he had to call the cellphone
he planted at the cemetery.

29:08.013 --> 29:10.581
Provenza:
Okay, so we know

29:10.583 --> 29:12.416
the phone number this asshole
is going to use

29:12.418 --> 29:14.251
to detonate the rest
of his bombs.

29:14.253 --> 29:16.186
Which means we can start
pinging his location...

29:16.188 --> 29:18.021
[ Beep ]
...right now. Buzz?

29:18.023 --> 29:19.857
Uh, here we go.
[ Taps keys ]

29:19.859 --> 29:21.759
[ Beep ]

29:26.532 --> 29:29.433
♪♪

29:29.435 --> 29:31.702
We have him. There he is.

29:31.704 --> 29:33.036
[ Beep ]

29:33.038 --> 29:34.872
He's across the street.

29:34.874 --> 29:37.040
At City Hall!

29:37.042 --> 29:38.876
It looks like
he's up in the tower.

29:38.878 --> 29:40.377
And the only good thing
about that is,

29:40.379 --> 29:41.612
considering
City Hall's security,

29:41.614 --> 29:43.046
he's probably not armed.

29:43.048 --> 29:44.748
No, but he can still
make calls.

29:44.750 --> 29:46.416
Buzz, the blocking!

29:46.418 --> 29:48.719
Six, sir. It's gonna take me
a couple of minutes.

29:48.721 --> 29:51.054
Buzz!
It's a process, sir.
Just give me two minutes.

29:51.056 --> 29:53.624
we need to take him down
where he is right now.

29:53.626 --> 29:55.893
If he sees a bunch of police
converging on City Hall,

29:55.895 --> 29:57.427
he'll start calling in
his C-4.

29:57.429 --> 29:58.896
And if he doesn't have a weapon,

29:58.898 --> 30:00.230
well, shooting him's
out of the question.

30:00.232 --> 30:02.065
He took our pictures
at the cemetery.

30:02.067 --> 30:04.635
He knows who we are. We can't
just walk up and grab him.

30:04.637 --> 30:06.069
<i> Buzz!</i>
12, sir.

30:06.071 --> 30:07.905
And yelling doesn't make it
go faster.

30:07.907 --> 30:10.641
Sharon: Mike, place City Hall
on lockdown, please.

30:10.643 --> 30:12.276
Yes, Ma'am.

30:12.278 --> 30:13.911
There's the matter of Liseth.

30:13.913 --> 30:15.612
He tried to blow her up first.

30:15.614 --> 30:17.447
We can't forget...
Lieutenant Mike Tao.

30:17.449 --> 30:19.950
...that he may still
be trying to kill her.

30:19.952 --> 30:21.618
We can worry about her later.

30:21.620 --> 30:23.420
She's here
where he can't get her.

30:23.422 --> 30:26.156
Buzz: 18. I'm almost there.
Almost there.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.125
I say that
we give him a warning.

30:28.127 --> 30:30.494
19. And... and...

30:30.496 --> 30:31.762
[ Beep ]
Blocked.

30:31.764 --> 30:33.463
Except for the cell
he used to call.

30:33.465 --> 30:35.265
All right, Captain,
what are you waiting for?

30:35.267 --> 30:37.768
The last time I called a killer
standing in a high place,

30:37.770 --> 30:39.136
he jumped.

30:39.138 --> 30:42.172
And the trouble with that is?

30:42.174 --> 30:45.242
♪♪

30:51.684 --> 30:54.718
[ Cellphone ringing ]

30:57.623 --> 30:59.957
Yeah?
<i>Cristian Ortiz,</i>

30:59.959 --> 31:02.860
<i> this is Captain Sharon Raydor</i>
<i> of the LAPD.</i>

31:02.862 --> 31:05.696
Oh. How can I help you,
Captain?

31:05.698 --> 31:08.165
By listening very closely.

31:08.167 --> 31:10.300
We have effectively blocked

31:10.302 --> 31:14.137
<i> every cellphone that you have</i>
<i> set up as a detonation device</i>

31:14.139 --> 31:16.306
<i> in every evidence locker</i>

31:16.308 --> 31:18.508
<i> in every division</i>
<i> you have compromised.</i>

31:18.510 --> 31:20.711
<i> City Hall is now on lockdown.</i>

31:20.713 --> 31:22.312
Shortly, you will be surrounded.

31:22.314 --> 31:25.349
My advice, sir --
Give yourself up.

31:25.351 --> 31:27.184
We will find you
an attorney and --

31:27.186 --> 31:30.120
And what?
We make a deal?!

31:31.323 --> 31:33.156
You got to be kidding me.

31:33.158 --> 31:35.325
There's no deal for me in this.

31:35.327 --> 31:39.162
I'm responsible for the death
of an LAPD civilian officer.

31:39.164 --> 31:42.499
I murdered my former
father-in-law in cold blood.

31:42.501 --> 31:44.735
But you didn't kill
Joseph Euley.

31:44.737 --> 31:48.705
Your ex-wife did that.
We know she framed you.

31:48.707 --> 31:51.608
<i> And we know how she did it.</i>

31:52.845 --> 31:55.545
♪♪

31:55.547 --> 31:57.347
You're lying.

31:57.349 --> 31:59.683
No. No, we're not lying.

31:59.685 --> 32:02.552
Now, listen, son, you've done
some terrible things,

32:02.554 --> 32:04.888
and -- and you're gonna
have to answer for them.

32:04.890 --> 32:08.692
But if you want your wife
to also pay for what she did,

32:08.694 --> 32:10.861
we need you to testify.

32:10.863 --> 32:14.698
You're ready to arrest her?
So...

32:14.700 --> 32:16.199
you have her there?

32:16.201 --> 32:18.568
Yes, we do.

32:18.570 --> 32:21.571
You wanna talk to me?

32:21.573 --> 32:24.541
Well, I wanna talk to her. Now.

32:24.543 --> 32:28.111
Hold on, sir.
We're almost there.

32:34.386 --> 32:36.954
Mr. Ortiz, you are here
with your ex-wife.

32:36.956 --> 32:38.722
You are on speaker.

32:38.724 --> 32:41.725
Wait. You're talking with
Cristian? You arrested him?

32:41.727 --> 32:43.894
<i> You listening to me,</i>
<i> you bitch?</i>

32:43.896 --> 32:46.763
<i> I spent 11 years in a box</i>
<i> because of you.</i>

32:46.765 --> 32:48.732
11 years!

32:48.734 --> 32:50.400
And now you're gonna pay.

32:50.402 --> 32:51.969
Okay, listen to this, sir.

32:51.971 --> 32:54.571
Liseth Ortiz,
you are under arrest...
What?

32:54.573 --> 32:55.806
...for murder
in the first degree...

32:55.808 --> 32:57.741
No!
...of Joseph Euley.

32:57.743 --> 32:59.576
Get your hands off of me!
You have the right
to remain silent.

32:59.578 --> 33:01.745
Anything you say can
and will be used against you
in a court of law.

33:01.747 --> 33:03.580
<i> You have the right</i>
<i> to an attorney.</i>

33:03.582 --> 33:04.982
<i> If you cannot afford one,</i>
<i> one will be appointed for you</i>

33:04.984 --> 33:06.416
by the state.
Cristian confessed to it.

33:06.418 --> 33:08.986
You framed him too well.
He had no choice.

33:08.988 --> 33:12.923
Mr. Ortiz,
Liseth will pay for this.

33:12.925 --> 33:15.292
<i> Oh, she'll pay,</i>
<i> but not how you think.</i>

33:15.294 --> 33:17.427
<i> I had to splurge after</i>
<i> the cemetery.</i>

33:17.429 --> 33:20.163
<i> I needed a couple of genuine</i>
<i> smartphones that I could use</i>

33:20.165 --> 33:21.999
to ping each other,
just like you pinged this

33:22.001 --> 33:24.167
crappy old disposable
we're talking on now.

33:24.169 --> 33:26.169
<i> That's right.</i>

33:26.171 --> 33:28.271
I got me two new phones.

33:28.273 --> 33:30.440
Well...

33:30.442 --> 33:32.175
only one with me.

33:32.177 --> 33:34.845
The other one is showing up
where I planted it.

33:34.847 --> 33:37.180
<i> Over there with you guys.</i>

33:37.182 --> 33:40.150
Gotta love these
phone-tracking apps.

33:40.152 --> 33:42.786
<i> Good luck finding it.</i>

33:42.788 --> 33:45.455
♪♪

33:45.457 --> 33:48.959
<i> Oh, by the way,</i>
<i> tell me, Captain,</i>

33:48.961 --> 33:52.429
how long have you had my bitch
of an ex-wife in custody?

33:57.536 --> 34:00.003
LAPD! Freeze, asshole!

34:00.005 --> 34:01.538
<i> Lose the phone</i>

34:01.540 --> 34:03.507
and get on your knees now!

34:03.509 --> 34:05.142
Or what?

34:05.144 --> 34:08.011
You'll shoot?
I'm unarmed.

34:08.013 --> 34:10.347
Yeah, well, you're a big guy,
and I feel threatened.

34:10.349 --> 34:12.682
<i>I'll take a chance! You wanna?!</i>
Andy!

34:12.684 --> 34:16.019
But if I'm under arrest,
aren't I allowed a phone call?

34:16.021 --> 34:19.556
It's a waste of time.
We disabled your IEDs.

34:19.558 --> 34:21.892
Really?

34:21.894 --> 34:24.227
♪♪

34:28.901 --> 34:31.234
The luggage!

34:31.236 --> 34:34.071
The bomb is in the luggage!
Everyone out!

34:34.073 --> 34:37.107
[ Screaming ]
Go! Go! Go!

34:42.681 --> 34:45.048
[ Cellphone rings ]

34:45.050 --> 34:48.151
[ Explosion ]

34:51.557 --> 34:53.190
[ Screaming ]

34:53.192 --> 34:56.660
[ Sirens wailing ]

35:03.035 --> 35:07.237
[ Electricity buzzing,
alarm blaring ]

35:07.239 --> 35:10.807
[ Alarm continues blaring ]

35:17.449 --> 35:21.451
[ Cellphone ringing ]

35:28.894 --> 35:30.927
Come on. Come on!

35:30.929 --> 35:32.929
[ Sirens wailing ]

35:32.931 --> 35:35.398
[ Cellphone ringing ]

35:35.400 --> 35:36.733
Flynn.

35:36.735 --> 35:39.936
Oh, Flynn, tell me you have
that son of a bitch.

35:39.938 --> 35:41.905
<i> Yeah, I got him. Are you okay?</i>

35:41.907 --> 35:44.274
How is everybody? Is Sh--
Is Sharon...

35:44.276 --> 35:45.609
Yeah, hold on.

35:45.611 --> 35:47.811
[ Sharon grunts ]
Hold on.

35:49.982 --> 35:52.949
[ Strained voice ] Andy,
what are you doing over there?

35:52.951 --> 35:54.784
It -- it's just a walk
across the street.

35:54.786 --> 35:56.786
And I'm the only guy
this asshole didn't know.

35:56.788 --> 35:58.655
I'm more worried about you guys.

35:58.657 --> 36:01.591
<i> Are you okay?</i>
[ Grunts ] I can tell you,

36:01.593 --> 36:04.928
the janitor's gonna have
a serious meltdown.

36:04.930 --> 36:06.763
[ Alarm continues blaring ]
We're okay.

36:06.765 --> 36:08.598
We all g--
We're gonna be okay.

36:08.600 --> 36:10.000
[ Coughing ]

36:15.607 --> 36:17.107
I should've shot you.

36:17.109 --> 36:19.109
♪♪

36:24.283 --> 36:25.849
Lucky for your mom
and everybody

36:25.851 --> 36:28.018
the bomb didn't hurt anyone.

36:29.621 --> 36:31.821
And I'm really glad
you weren't there.

36:31.823 --> 36:33.790
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

36:33.792 --> 36:36.526
Look, I-I gotta get going.
Aiden asked me to come in

36:36.528 --> 36:38.628
and work a little early
to help prep for a party --
Uh, listen, Gus,

36:38.630 --> 36:40.630
I've been thinking ever since
we spoke about it --
My Uber's coming.

36:40.632 --> 36:42.499
I know -- Sorry.
This will just take a second.

36:42.501 --> 36:43.684
I've been thinking about it,
Gus,

36:43.685 --> 36:44.868
and the next time
I visit you at work,

36:44.870 --> 36:46.970
I want it to be in Napa.

36:46.972 --> 36:48.605
What?

36:50.309 --> 36:53.843
I didn't -- I didn't know
that, um...

36:53.845 --> 36:55.812
So much
of what we were doing,

36:55.814 --> 36:58.481
I didn't understand

36:58.483 --> 37:00.850
it was on my terms.

37:00.852 --> 37:02.485
And that's wrong.

37:02.487 --> 37:04.321
And we can't do it anymore.

37:04.323 --> 37:05.889
But if -- if you're going
to stay here...

37:05.891 --> 37:07.691
I am.

37:07.693 --> 37:10.060
But this opportunity in Napa,
it's -- it's...

37:10.062 --> 37:11.828
it's what's best
for your career,

37:11.830 --> 37:13.330
which is every bit
as important as mine.

37:13.332 --> 37:15.732
So we'll...

37:15.734 --> 37:18.335
we'll try
the long-distance thing.

37:18.337 --> 37:21.671
Besides, I'll be too busy here
to get into any trouble.

37:21.673 --> 37:23.406
And I'm sure that
Aiden will...

37:23.408 --> 37:25.575
Aiden will keep you
very busy, too.

37:27.346 --> 37:30.013
I'm not asking you for this.
I know.

37:30.015 --> 37:32.182
I'm doing it
because I love you, Gus,

37:32.184 --> 37:35.218
and because I want you
to be happy.

37:35.220 --> 37:38.355
And you deserve
to be with, um...

37:38.357 --> 37:40.724
Where. Where.
You deserve to be

37:40.726 --> 37:43.393
<i> where</i> you'll be happy.

37:43.395 --> 37:46.863
[ Chuckles ]

37:46.865 --> 37:49.766
Rusty. [ Laughs ]

37:51.036 --> 37:52.435
You always surprise me.

37:53.772 --> 37:57.240
[ Breathes deeply ]

37:57.242 --> 37:58.942
Okay.

37:58.944 --> 38:01.244
[ Chuckles, sniffles ]

38:01.246 --> 38:03.613
We're gonna make this
a good thing, all right?

38:03.615 --> 38:06.549
And then you can come up,
and I'll be coming down here.

38:06.551 --> 38:07.917
[ Chuckles ]

38:07.919 --> 38:09.586
And we'll be stronger
for it in the end.

38:09.588 --> 38:12.289
Right. Definitely.

38:12.291 --> 38:14.257
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

38:14.259 --> 38:16.293
Your Uber.

38:25.070 --> 38:27.637
Thank you.

38:34.646 --> 38:36.746
[ Door opens ]
[ Breathes sharply ]

38:36.748 --> 38:38.548
[ Door closes ]

38:40.752 --> 38:42.552
Goodbye.

38:43.789 --> 38:45.789
Fritz:
Well, it all worked out.

38:45.791 --> 38:49.092
But before we go on,
I, uh, I just wanna say

38:49.094 --> 38:51.328
if not for you,

38:51.330 --> 38:53.263
we'd be cleaning up
a mess like this

38:53.265 --> 38:55.265
at every division in the city.

38:55.267 --> 38:57.500
And more officers
would have died.

38:58.470 --> 39:02.272
Ortiz may be nuts,
but planting C-4

39:02.274 --> 39:05.108
inside items we'd pick up
from crime scenes

39:05.110 --> 39:06.843
was a smart plan.
-Mm.

39:06.845 --> 39:09.612
Depraved, but smart.

39:09.614 --> 39:11.948
Can you take a minute?
Mm.

39:11.950 --> 39:15.652
Yeah, join me in the, uh...

39:15.654 --> 39:17.954
Assistant Chief's Office?

39:17.956 --> 39:20.156
For something which I think
is a good surprise.

39:20.158 --> 39:22.459
Oh, my God.

39:22.461 --> 39:24.294
If you're not Assistant Chief --

39:24.296 --> 39:25.528
You are being asked for.

39:25.530 --> 39:27.197
That is not a good surprise.

39:27.199 --> 39:28.832
The alternative would've been
Winnie Davis.

39:28.834 --> 39:31.801
Just come with me, Captain...

39:31.803 --> 39:35.138
if I can still call you that
for the next minute or so.

39:35.140 --> 39:37.807
This is it.
She's Assistant Chief.

39:37.809 --> 39:39.042
Or it's Fritz.

39:39.044 --> 39:40.310
Anyone but Davis.

39:40.312 --> 39:42.479
It has to be the Captain.

39:42.481 --> 39:44.481
Can they ignore
what she just did here?

39:44.483 --> 39:47.684
[ Scoffs ]
Oh, yeah? Watch.

39:47.686 --> 39:50.019
[ Laughs ]
Hey, check this out.

39:50.021 --> 39:52.856
Roaches, rats, and Provenza.
[ Clack ]

39:52.858 --> 39:54.657
They can survive anything.

39:54.659 --> 39:56.926
[ Laughs ]
[ Rattles ]

40:02.834 --> 40:05.402
Looks like I drew
the short straw.

40:05.404 --> 40:08.905
Congratulations, Leo!

40:08.907 --> 40:13.343
Oh, this is an excellent,
excellent choice.

40:13.345 --> 40:14.711
I couldn't agree more.

40:14.713 --> 40:16.413
And I truly appreciate
you allowing me

40:16.415 --> 40:18.915
to keep my old office
at Piper Tech,

40:18.917 --> 40:22.152
which I'm about to go back to
right now, if you'll excuse me.

40:23.221 --> 40:25.388
Oh, and, uh...

40:25.390 --> 40:27.257
congrats to you, too, Sharon.

40:27.259 --> 40:29.259
[ Door closes ]

40:29.261 --> 40:32.429
Would it be out of line
for me to say

40:32.431 --> 40:34.898
how relieved I am?
[ Laughs ]

40:34.900 --> 40:36.733
Not at all.

40:36.735 --> 40:39.369
Though your work may be
a<i> little</i> bit more difficult.

40:39.371 --> 40:40.770
Oh?

40:40.772 --> 40:42.405
Fortunately,

40:42.407 --> 40:44.874
Commander Raydor,

40:44.876 --> 40:46.543
I think you're up to the job.

40:46.545 --> 40:48.611
Commander?

40:55.587 --> 40:57.454
Welcome to the top brass.

41:00.392 --> 41:02.125
I'm not about giving officers
more responsibility

41:02.127 --> 41:03.793
without the authority
to go with it.

41:08.400 --> 41:11.234
Oh, my God.

41:11.236 --> 41:14.170
Oh, dear.

41:15.974 --> 41:18.608
I'd completely let go of this.
I didn't --

41:18.610 --> 41:20.310
I didn't think...

41:22.747 --> 41:24.514
Thank you, Chief.

41:30.755 --> 41:33.289
Well...

41:33.291 --> 41:34.891
have a seat.

41:37.162 --> 41:39.429
Let me tell you

41:39.431 --> 41:42.832
how I'd like to change
Major Crimes...

41:44.769 --> 41:46.302
...into something better.

41:46.304 --> 41:48.438
Okay.

41:48.440 --> 41:50.807
[ Laughs ]

41:50.809 --> 41:52.876
♪♪
